ture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705191,"age":19,"year":"1315","toYear":"1317","julianDay":2201354,"title":"Famine Strikes Europe","description":"A famine caused by cold winters and wet summers across Europe caused millions to die due to starvation. Desperation from hunger caused high levels of crime, stampedes in bread lines in London, infanticide, and even cannibalism throughout Europe.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705192,"age":32,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When William D'Aumarle was born about 1296, in Woodbury with Exton, Devon, England, his father, Geoffrey d'Aumarle, was 11294 and his mother, Joan Pomeroy, was 22. He married Isabel Meriet about 1315, in England. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1335, in Lympstone, Devon, England, at the age of 40."},"et":{"Abt 1296–1335":"umbes 1296–1335","1296–1335":"1296–1335","1295–1370":"1295–1370","1320–1361":"1320–1361","1268–1321":"1268–1321","1276–Female":"1276–Surnud","before 21 February 1321":"enne 21. veebruari 1321","1296":"1296","1361":"1361","1295":"1295","1370":"1370","Abt 1296":"umbes 1296","1315":"1315","1335":"1335","1268":"1268","1321":"1321","about 1315":"umbes 1315","1320":"1320","1276":"1276","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","England":"England","Lympstone, Devon, England":"Lympstone, Devon, England","Cornwall, England":"Cornwall, England","Woodbury with Exton, Devon, England":"Woodbury with Exton, Devon, England"},"fi":{"Abt 1296–1335":"noin 1296–1335","1296–1335":"1296–1335","1295–1370":"1295–1370","1320–1361":"1320–1361","1268–1321":"1268–1321","1276–Female":"1276–Kuollut","before 21 February 1321":"ennen vuotta 21. helmikuuta 1321","1296":"12